{
  "page": "Turncloak",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table style=\"margin: 4px 10%; border: 1px solid #aaa; background:#fbfbfb;\"><tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"padding: 2px 0 2px 0.5em;border-left: 10px solid #f28500;\">\n<div style=\"width: 50px;\"><img alt=\"Content.png\" src=\"/images/c/cc/Content.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" />\n</div></td><td style=\"border: none; padding: 0.25em 0.9em; width: 100%;\"> This article or section is a <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stub\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"wikipedia:Stub\">stub</a>. You can help \"A Wiki Of Ice And Fire\" by <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://awoiaf.westeros.org/index.php?title=Turncloak&amp;action=edit\">expanding it</a> and/or improving existing text.</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:402px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Marc_Scheff_dubious_loyalties.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/8/84/Marc_Scheff_dubious_loyalties.jpg/400px-Marc_Scheff_dubious_loyalties.jpg\" width=\"400\" height=\"267\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/8/84/Marc_Scheff_dubious_loyalties.jpg 1.5x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Marc_Scheff_dubious_loyalties.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>A soldier turns his cloak. © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:402px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Raymond_Bonilla_turncloak.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/61/Raymond_Bonilla_turncloak.jpg/400px-Raymond_Bonilla_turncloak.jpg\" width=\"400\" height=\"309\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/6/61/Raymond_Bonilla_turncloak.jpg 1.5x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Raymond_Bonilla_turncloak.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The Turncloak - by Raymond Bonilla. © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>A <b>turncloak</b> is the term used for a treacherous, disloyal person who has betrayed those who put their faith in them, those who previously considered the turncloak loyal and worthy of trust. The term comes from turning your cloak from the <a href=\"/index.php/Heraldry\" title=\"Heraldry\">heraldry</a> of your original loyalties to that of your new master.\n</p><p>The betrayal is often an act of double-crossing, suddenly changing alliances and going over to the enemy, et al. To name someone a turncloak is to name them the worst kind of betrayer and traitor. \n</p><p>A person may turn their cloak to benefit themselves, or for more personal reasons to change their loyalty. <a href=\"/index.php/Sellswords\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sellswords\">Sellswords</a> have a reputation for being willing to betray anyone for enough gold.\n</p><p>Once a person is considered a turncloak, they can become a pariah and no one will put their trust in them or ever respect them, not even the people who greatly benefited from their betrayal.   \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Turncloaks\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Turncloaks</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Accused_turncloaks\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Accused turncloaks</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#A_Clash_of_Kings\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">7</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Turncloaks\">Turncloaks</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Turncloak&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Turncloaks\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Ulf_White\" title=\"Ulf White\">Ulf White</a> - betrayed the <a href=\"/index.php/Blacks\" title=\"Blacks\">blacks</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Hugh_Hammer\" title=\"Hugh Hammer\">Hugh Hammer</a> - betrayed the <a href=\"/index.php/Blacks\" title=\"Blacks\">blacks</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Mance_Rayder\" title=\"Mance Rayder\">Mance Rayder</a> - betrayed the <a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Night&#39;s Watch\">Night's Watch</a> to return to the <a href=\"/index.php/Free_Folk\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Free Folk\">Free Folk</a> of his birth</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Theon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Theon Greyjoy\">Theon Greyjoy</a> - betrayed <a href=\"/index.php/Robb_Stark\" title=\"Robb Stark\">Robb Stark</a> for House Greyjoy</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Vargo_Hoat\" title=\"Vargo Hoat\">Vargo Hoat</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Brave_Companions\" title=\"Brave Companions\">Brave Companions</a> - betrayed their employer <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">House Lannister</a> when paid by <a href=\"/index.php/Roose_Bolton\" title=\"Roose Bolton\">Roose Bolton</a> to turn to <a href=\"/index.php/House_Stark\" title=\"House Stark\">House Stark</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok47.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok47.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Roose_Bolton\" title=\"Roose Bolton\">Roose Bolton</a> - betrayed <a href=\"/index.php/House_Stark\" title=\"House Stark\">House Stark</a> and King <a href=\"/index.php/Robb_Stark\" title=\"Robb Stark\">Robb Stark</a>’s cause</li>\n<li>The <a href=\"/index.php/Stormcrows\" title=\"Stormcrows\">Stormcrows</a> - betrayed their <a href=\"/index.php/Yunkish\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Yunkish\">Yunkish</a> employers to turn to <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Accused_turncloaks\">Accused turncloaks</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Turncloak&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Accused turncloaks\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Luthor_Largent\" title=\"Luthor Largent\">Luthor Largent</a> - Commander of the <a href=\"/index.php/City_Watch_of_King%27s_Landing\" title=\"City Watch of King&#39;s Landing\">City Watch of King's Landing</a>, accused of turning cloak from King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon II Targaryen\">Aegon II Targaryen</a> to Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen\">Rhaenyra Targaryen</a>, but he said the gold cloaks had always been loyal to their former commander <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_Targaryen\" title=\"Daemon Targaryen\">Daemon Targaryen</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a> - <a href=\"/index.php/Qhorin_Halfhand\" title=\"Qhorin Halfhand\">Qhorin Halfhand</a> ordered Jon to yield to the <a href=\"/index.php/Wildlings\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Wildlings\">wildlings</a> and act as a spy. Some men of the <a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Night&#39;s Watch\">Night's Watch</a>, such as <a href=\"/index.php/Janos_Slynt\" title=\"Janos Slynt\">Janos Slynt</a>, think Jon went over willingly and name Jon a turncloak.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Sybell_Spicer\" title=\"Sybell Spicer\">Sybell Spicer</a> - named a scheming turncloak bitch by Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime Lannister</a>.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Turncloak&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Turncloak&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Clash_of_Kings\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Turncloak&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Clash of Kings\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>At the <a href=\"/index.php/Siege_of_Storm%27s_End_(299)\" title=\"Siege of Storm&#39;s End (299)\">siege</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Storm%27s_End\" title=\"Storm&#39;s End\">Storm's End</a>, King <a href=\"/index.php/Renly_Baratheon\" title=\"Renly Baratheon\">Renly Baratheon</a> is killed by a <a href=\"/index.php/Shadow_child\" title=\"Shadow child\">shadow</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Assassin\" title=\"Assassin\">assassin</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Afterwards, the majority of the host that had accompanied him to Storm's End swears their allegiance to his brother, King <a href=\"/index.php/Stannis_Baratheon\" title=\"Stannis Baratheon\">Stannis Baratheon</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> When Stannis confronts Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Cortnay_Penrose\" title=\"Cortnay Penrose\">Cortnay Penrose</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Castellan\" title=\"Castellan\">castellan</a> of Storm's End, Cortnay refuses to yield the castle and accuses the host of being turncloaks. This angers the king's men, and Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Bryce_Caron\" title=\"Bryce Caron\">Bryce Caron</a> denies that any man there is a turncloak. However, <a href=\"/index.php/Davos_Seaworth\" title=\"Davos Seaworth\">Davos Seaworth</a> feels that Cortnay is not entirely wrong.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Turncloak&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_Targaryen\" title=\"Daemon Targaryen\">Daemon</a> gave us <a href=\"/index.php/Gold_cloaks\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gold cloaks\">these cloaks</a>, and they're gold no matter how you turn them.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Luthor_Largent\" title=\"Luthor Largent\">Luthor Largent</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Gwayne_Hightower\" title=\"Gwayne Hightower\">Gwayne Hightower</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b><a href=\"/index.php/Arya_Stark\" title=\"Arya Stark\">Arya Stark</a></b>: You hated Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Amory_Lorch\" title=\"Amory Lorch\">Amory</a> too.<br />\n<b><a href=\"/index.php/Gendry\" title=\"Gendry\">Gendry</a></b>: I hate this lot worse. Ser Amory was fighting for <a href=\"/index.php/Tywin_Lannister\" title=\"Tywin Lannister\">his lord</a>, but the <a href=\"/index.php/Brave_Companions\" title=\"Brave Companions\">Mummers</a> are <a href=\"/index.php/Sellsword\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sellsword\">sellswords</a> and turncloaks.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok64.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok64.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></p></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><i>Turncloak</i>. The name was bitter as bile.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok66.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok66.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Theon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Theon Greyjoy\">Theon Greyjoy</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>A <a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Night&#39;s Watch\">black cloak</a> can't be turned.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok66.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok66.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Theon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Theon Greyjoy\">Theon Greyjoy</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>How do I play the turncloak without becoming one?<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>You're the one they call Turncloak. Why should we believe your promises?<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Dagon_Codd\" title=\"Dagon Codd\">Dagon Codd</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Theon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Theon Greyjoy\">Theon Greyjoy</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>I know who the dwarf is, and what he is. <a href=\"/index.php/Kinslayer\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Kinslayer\">Kinslayer</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Kingslayer\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Kingslayer\">kingslayer</a>, murderer, turncloak. <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">Lannister</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;the <a href=\"/index.php/Widow_of_the_waterfront\" title=\"Widow of the waterfront\">widow of the waterfront</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Jorah_Mormont\" title=\"Jorah Mormont\">Jorah Mormont</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Your <a href=\"/index.php/Sellsword\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sellsword\">sellswords</a> once served your foes, and once a man turns his cloak he will not scruple to turn it again.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Barristan_Selmy\" title=\"Barristan Selmy\">Barristan Selmy</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>\"Theon Turncloak,\" someone said as he passed.  Other men turned away at the sight of him.  One spat.  <i>And why not?</i> He was the traitor who had taken <a href=\"/index.php/Winterfell\" title=\"Winterfell\">Winterfell</a> by treachery, slain his foster brothers, delivered his own people to be flayed at <a href=\"/index.php/Moat_Cailin\" title=\"Moat Cailin\">Moat Cailin</a>, and given his foster sister to <a href=\"/index.php/Ramsay_Snow\" title=\"Ramsay Snow\">Lord Ramsay</a>'s bed.  <a href=\"/index.php/Roose_Bolton\" title=\"Roose Bolton\">Roose Bolton</a> might make use of him, but true <a href=\"/index.php/Northmen\" title=\"Northmen\">northmen</a> must despise him.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup></p></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>I have done terrible things… betrayed my own, turned my cloak, ordered the death of men who trusted me… but I am no <a href=\"/index.php/Kinslayer\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Kinslayer\">kinslayer</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Theon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Theon Greyjoy\">Theon Greyjoy</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Rowan\" title=\"Rowan\">Rowan</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><a href=\"/index.php/Mance_Rayder\" title=\"Mance Rayder\">Mance Rayder</a> swore an oath as well. He vowed to wear no crowns, take no wife, father no sons. Then he turned his cloak, did all those things, and led a fearsome host against the realm.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_14-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Bowen_Marsh\" title=\"Bowen Marsh\">Bowen Marsh</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Turncloak&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Racok47.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok47.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings-Chapter_47\" title=\"A Clash of Kings-Chapter 47\">Chapter 47</a>, Arya IX.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Racok33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings-Chapter_33\" title=\"A Clash of Kings-Chapter 33\">Chapter 33</a>, Catelyn IV.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Racok36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings-Chapter_36\" title=\"A Clash of Kings-Chapter 36\">Chapter 36</a>, Tyrion VIII.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Racok42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-